commit.message:
- In xfrd del secondarty zone, the timer could perhaps have
  event_added, and if so, it would not be event_del if a tcp connection
  is active at the time. This could cause the libevent event lists
  to fail. Also fix to make sure to set event_added for the
  nsd-control ssl nonblocking handshake and check event_added there
  too, for extra certainty.
- Fix compile with memclean for xfrd nsd.db close.

netio_dispatch timeout 1 sec for fast reaping

In the server_main(). To reap children that took long to exit and exited after
the initial reaping at the start of the server_main loop.
reap old-serve processed in reload process

test package for <defunct> processes

For the case when TCP session holds one server processes alive during a reload.
The others exit and become <defunct> because of a blocking read in
server_reload().
